 Downloading & Installing Microsoft SQL Server

This document summarizes the setup process followed in **Video 1** of the Insurance Dashboard project, where Microsoft SQL Server and SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) were installed.

What I Did in This Step

- Downloaded **Microsoft SQL Server 2022 Developer Edition** from the official Microsoft website.
- Chose **Basic installation type** for simplicity.
- Installed **SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)** for writing and executing SQL queries.
- Launched SSMS and connected to the local SQL Server instance using **Windows Authentication**.
- Verified successful setup by opening a new query window in SSMS.


Tools & Versions

Tool                     Version / Details                    

SQL Server               2019 Developer Edition                 
 SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) | Latest version (from Microsoft site) 
Installation Type        Basic                                 
Authentication Method   Windows Authentication                

Download Links

- SQL Server 2022 Developer Edition](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/sql-server/sql-server-downloads
- SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/ssms/download-sql-server-management-studio-ssms

---

 Notes

- Make sure to **select “Database Engine”** as the server type while connecting.
- In real-world companies, server credentials are provided to you. But for this project, a local setup is used.
